38
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,240
when the contract has already been finalized,

39
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:37,040
yet here I am still analyzing it.

40
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,860
The contract has been finalized?

41
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,680
It's going to be signed at tomorrow's press conference.

42
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:46,280
All the legal procedures have been completed.

43
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,240
Then what are you worried about?

44
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:53,250
I've discovered a problem.

45
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,520
What?

46
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,640
Look at these contracts.

47
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:01,370
This subcontracting company.

48
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,860
Is there something wrong with this company?

49
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,580
I specifically investigated this company,

50
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,320
and I found that

51
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,180
it actually doesn't exist at all,

52
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,520
yet it's receiving

53
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:15,520
investments from both Snow Leopard and Wanqi Groups.

54
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,570
You investigated this?

55
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,660
You went yourself?

56
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,800
Yes, of course.

57
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,360
I see.

58
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,079
Chang Ming,

59
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:30,120
I didn't expect you to pull something this big.

60
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,520
What?

61
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:32,880
So,

62
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:35,920
this company is probably just a shell company.

63
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:38,520
They only exist to raise money through going public.

64
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:40,440
They're taking advantage of the merger

65
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,300
to cash in when stock prices rise,

66
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,490
and then they'll declare bankruptcy.

67
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,680
Stop.

68
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:48,760
What's wrong?

69
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:52,020
Have you forgotten what happened to our family?

70
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:56,290
Have you forgotten that our father...

71
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,040
No,

72
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:06,240
I must stop this from happening.

73
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:07,810
Once you do this,

74
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,480
you can never return to Wanqi Group.

75
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,560
I know,

76
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:14,640
but I have to do it.

77
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,490
I've made up my mind.

78
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,600
But

79
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:21,570
the press conference is tomorrow.

80
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,560
I have a plan.

81
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,040
Distinguished leaders and guests,

82
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,760
the Snow Leopard Group signing ceremony

83
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:34,320
is now officially beginning.

84
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:37,120
Thank you all for attending our signing ceremony.

85
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,520
Now, please welcome the Acting President

86
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,650
of Snow Leopard Group, Mr. Chang Ming.

87
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:45,080
First of all, thank you everyone for coming today.

88
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:47,140
The partnership with Wanqi Group

89
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:50,080
represents a significant upgrade for our Snow Leopard Group.

90
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:53,400
Moving forward, our group will enter a transformation period.

91
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,080
We pledge

92
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,600
to put consumer interests first

93
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:59,900
and deliver higher quality products to our customers.

94
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,400
Now we'll move on to the interview segment.

95
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:06,960
We've just received a whistleblower document

96
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:07,640
which claims

97
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:08,720
that the purpose of this merger

98
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,440
is merely to create market hype,

99
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,960
while the actual profits don't go to either company

100
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:15,360
but to a third-party company called Morning Star.

101
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:17,290
Could you explain what's going on?

102
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:18,760
The document also includes

103
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:20,000
evidence of related contracts.

104
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:20,760
Is this true?

105
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,600
Does this Morning Star company

106
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,600
actually exist?

107
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,080
Is it true as the document states

108
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:26,600
that it's just a shell company created

109
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,260
to raise money through an IPO?

110
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:30,100
These are dual contracts.

111
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,450
Let me go in with you.

112
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:34,760
No need,

113
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,580
I'm sure I can handle this.

114
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,080
Please don't be influenced by these

115
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,760
irrelevant pieces of information.

116
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:46,680
Please carefully evaluate rumors that lack evidence.

117
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,640
I have evidence.

118
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,080
I'm a lawyer from

119
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:55,080
the legal department of Wanqi Group.

120
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,560
The contract in my hand can prove everything.

121
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,320
Everyone can see

122
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,650
